# Controllers

## Structure

```java
@RestController
@RequestMapping("/api/users")
public class UsersController {
    private final IUserService _service;
    // constructor injection only
}
```

## Rules

- Return `ResponseEntity<APIResponse<T>>`.
- Use `@RequestBody` for JSON POST/PATCH bodies — **required** (vendor endpoints must not omit it).
- Multipart: `@RequestPart` for files + captcha (see `changeAvatar`).
- Path prefix: `/api/{resource}` — lowercase, plural nouns.
- No business logic; no direct repository access.

## HTTP verbs

| Verb | Use |
|------|-----|
| GET | Read |
| POST | Create, actions (login, alive) |
| PATCH | Partial update |
| DELETE | Soft-delete via proc (void flag) |

## Documentation

Javadoc on class and public methods describing params, return type, and thrown exceptions.
